      "kwargs": {
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "{\"success\":true,\"process_rule_id\":\"J09B\",\"process_rule\":\"1. Copy the decision table rows into table `J09B_temp` for all tours that start with `J09B`.\\n\\n2. Add column `ENTSCHEIDUNG` to `J09B_temp`.\\n\\n3. Classify the meter reading type in `J09B_temp`.\\n   - Set `ENTSCHEIDUNG` to `KSA` when a `HAUS` has less than 3 `EQUNR`.\\n   - Else set `ENTSCHEIDUNG` to `EVU`.\\n   - Set all houses with `HOUSE_NUM1 = 0` to `EVU`.\\n\\n4. Join `J09B_temp` with the `EABLG` table using `INSTALLATION`.\\n\\n5. Join the result with `SALES_MASTER` and `NET_MASTER` using `EQUNR`.\\n\\n6. Compare customer data from `SALES_MASTER` and `NET_MASTER`.\\n\\n7. If sales customer data is not empty:\\n   1. Use the customer entries from the sales customer data table.\\n   Else:\\n   1. Use the customer entries from the net customer data table.\\n\\n8. Export the final table as CSV file named `J09B`.\\n   - Use these exact column names in the export:\\n     `Meter Reading (MR) Doc. No.`, `HAUS`, `ANLAGE`, `ME_MA_ID`, `EQUNR`, `HOUSE_NUM1`, `ENTSCHEIDUNG`, `TITLE`, `FORENAME`, `SURNAME`, `STREET`, `STREETNO`, `POST_CODE1`, `CITY1`, `CITY2`, `EMAIL`\\n\\n9. Send an email to `meter.readings@evu.com` with the CSV file attached.\\n   - `file_path: <path_to_exported_csv_file>`\\n\\n10. Delete the temporary table.\\n\\n11. End the process.\"}",
            "id": "lc_da9f1e85-403d-4141-927d-3c9b945f21ce"
          }
        ],
        "type": "tool",
        "name": "retrieve_process",
        "id": "19fb2bfd-3530-46a1-b06d-8d8c09c91a88",
        "tool_call_id": "call_xfzQDr9exzRpc3MqlH1fxXml",
        "artifact": {
          "structured_content": {
            "success": true,
            "process_rule_id": "J09B",
            "process_rule": "1. Copy the decision table rows into table `J09B_temp` for all tours that start with `J09B`.\n\n2. Add column `ENTSCHEIDUNG` to `J09B_temp`.\n\n3. Classify the meter reading type in `J09B_temp`.\n   - Set `ENTSCHEIDUNG` to `KSA` when a `HAUS` has less than 3 `EQUNR`.\n   - Else set `ENTSCHEIDUNG` to `EVU`.\n   - Set all houses with `HOUSE_NUM1 = 0` to `EVU`.\n\n4. Join `J09B_temp` with the `EABLG` table using `INSTALLATION`.\n\n5. Join the result with `SALES_MASTER` and `NET_MASTER` using `EQUNR`.\n\n6. Compare customer data from `SALES_MASTER` and `NET_MASTER`.\n\n7. If sales customer data is not empty:\n   1. Use the customer entries from the sales customer data table.\n   Else:\n   1. Use the customer entries from the net customer data table.\n\n8. Export the final table as CSV file named `J09B`.\n   - Use these exact column names in the export:\n     `Meter Reading (MR) Doc. No.`, `HAUS`, `ANLAGE`, `ME_MA_ID`, `EQUNR`, `HOUSE_NUM1`, `ENTSCHEIDUNG`, `TITLE`, `FORENAME`, `SURNAME`, `STREET`, `STREETNO`, `POST_CODE1`, `CITY1`, `CITY2`, `EMAIL`\n\n9. Send an email to `meter.readings@evu.com` with the CSV file attached.\n   - `file_path: <path_to_exported_csv_file>`\n\n10. Delete the temporary table.\n\n11. End the process."
          }
        },
        "status": "success"
      }
    },
